=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides a summary of the properties of a data deletion job. For a
complete listing, call the DescribeDataDeletionJob
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/personalize/latest/dg/API_DescribeDataDeletionJob.html)
API operation.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CreationDateTime => Str

The creation date and time (in Unix time) of the data deletion job.


=head2 DataDeletionJobArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data deletion job.


=head2 DatasetGroupArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the dataset group the job deleted
records from.


=head2 FailureReason => Str

If a data deletion job fails, provides the reason why.


=head2 JobName => Str

The name of the data deletion job.


=head2 LastUpdatedDateTime => Str

The date and time (in Unix time) the data deletion job was last
updated.


=head2 Status => Str

The status of the data deletion job.

A data deletion job can have one of the following statuses:

=over

=item *

PENDING E<gt> IN_PROGRESS E<gt> COMPLETED -or- FAILED

=back




